# Leaderboard AI metadata — under ruling B a signed-in won daily run auto-submits
# under the account name, tagging which AI assistant helped. The tool is resolved
# inference-first (a companion co-play is auto-tagged); when it is neither
# inferable nor stored, the settlement asks once inline with SSOT chips and
# remembers the pick. The redundant free-nickname + AI-model modal is retired.

Feature: Leaderboard AI metadata
  As a BombSquad daily player
  I want my leaderboard score to carry the AI assistant I used
  So that leaderboard rows compare runs with their AI context intact

  Background:
    Given my viewport width is 375 pixels
    And I open /

  # Source: leaderboard-ai-metadata
  @playwright
  Scenario: A first daily win auto-submits under my name with the AI assistant I picked
    Given I am signed in with the leaderboard name "小明"
    And I have just defused the bomb in a daily run and the result page is open
    And no leaderboard AI metadata is stored on this device
    Then the result page asks which AI I played with

    When I pick AI assistant "Claude" in the settlement
    Then the result page shows my global rank
    And the leaderboard submission carries nickname "小明" and AI assistant "claude"
